==English==

===Adjective===
'''tactual'''

# [guess:] able to be actually touched.
#:'' This may not be a 'real' word.  I came across it on the web, in a sentence fragment saying "sometimes I am fighting for my own sanity, attempting to reconcile the tactual world with a world which can neither be seen, heard or touched." My guess is that it is maybe a cross between "tactical" and "factual" - or maybe, it is a combination of "tactile" and "actual" - maybe with some influence of  "tactful" and  "virtual". and maybe also "textual" and "sensual".''